        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 2:59PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 259 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Penrose, or 20 miles west of Pueblo, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Penrose.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
